###Representing the altitudes

The purple balloon started from sea level and climbed $2.5$ meters per second.

$\begin{align}
\text{altitude}_\text{purple balloon}&=2.5\,\dfrac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}\cdot t + 0\,\text{m}\\\\
&=\purpleD{2.5t\,\dfrac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}}
\end{align}$

The gold balloon started from $15$ meters above sea level and climbed $2$ meters per second.

$\begin{align}
\text{altitude}_\text{gold balloon}&=2\,\dfrac{\text{m}}{\text{s}}\cdot t + 15\,\text{m}\\\\
&=\goldE{2t\,\dfrac{\text{m}}{\text{s}} + 15\,\text{m}}
\end{align}$

###Representing the distances

Xóchitl pedals at a rate of $18\,\dfrac{\text{km}}{\text{h}}$, which means she pedals $\dfrac{18\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}}$.

$\begin{align}
\text{distance}_\text{X}&=\dfrac{18\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}} \cdot t\\\\
&=\goldE{\dfrac{3\,\text{km}}{10\,\text{min}} \cdot t}
\end{align}$

Cowessess pedals for $12$ more minutes than Xóchitl does. He pedals at a rate of $\dfrac{10\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}}$.

$\begin{align}
\text{distance}_\text{C}&=\dfrac{10\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}} \cdot (t+12\,\text{min})\\\\
&=\purpleD{\dfrac{1\,\text{km}}{6\,\text{min}} \cdot (t+12\,\text{min})}
\end{align}$

###Representing the amounts

The computer has rendered $540\,\text{kpx}$ of the kitchen scene and renders $90\,\text{kpx}$ more each minute. 

$\begin{align}
\text{amount}_\text{kitchen}&=\goldE{90\,\dfrac{\text{kpx}}{\text{min}}\cdot t + 540\,\text{kpx}}
\end{align}$

The computer has rendered $960\,\text{kpx}$ of the garden scene and renders $60\,\text{kpx}$ more each minute. 

$\begin{align}
\text{amount}_\text{garden}&=\purpleD{60\,\dfrac{\text{kpx}}{\text{min}}\cdot t + 960\,\text{kpx}}
\end{align}$

###Representing the numbers of beads

Aspen has $306$ green beads and uses $40$ green beads for every $5\,\text{cm}$ of the belt.

$\begin{align}
\text{beads}_\text{green}&=\goldE{306\,\text{beads}-\dfrac{40\,\text{beads}}{5\,\text{cm}}\cdot \ell}
\end{align}$

Aspen has $210$ silver beads and uses $24$ silver beads for every $5\,\text{cm}$ of the belt.

$\begin{align}
\text{beads}_\text{silver}&=\purpleD{210\,\text{beads}-\dfrac{24\,\text{beads}}{5\,\text{cm}}\cdot \ell}
\end{align}$

###Representing the distances

Jaquan jogs at a rate of $9\,\dfrac{\text{km}}{\text{h}}$, which means he jogs $\dfrac{9\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}}$.

$\begin{align}
\text{distance}_{\text{J}}&={\dfrac{9\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}}\cdot t}\\\\
&=\goldE{\dfrac{3\,\text{km}}{20\,\text{min}}\cdot t}
\end{align}$

Odalis runs for $2$ fewer minutes than Jaquan does. They run at a rate of $\dfrac{12\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}}$.

$\begin{align}
\text{distance}_{\text{O}} &={\dfrac{12\,\text{km}}{60\,\text{min}}\cdot (t-2\,\text{min})}\\\\
&={\dfrac{1\,\text{km}}{5\,\text{min}}\cdot (t-2\,\text{min})}\\\\
&=\purpleD{\dfrac{1\,\text{km}}{5\,\text{min}}\cdot t-\dfrac{2}{5}\,\text{km}}
\end{align}$
